    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Standard">
        <prj:name>Resolve the kinematical structure of the disk</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We are aimed to explore the morphological, velocity and temperature structure of the molecular disk in a radius range of 150-850 AU}. To achieve this we will perform molecular line observations at band 7 of transitions that from previous SMA observations we know are bright (Fig.2; see Table~1 for the list of lines to be observed). We plan to use a set of tools to model the molecular disk and derive fundamental physical properties (e.g., disk and stellar mass, the accretion rate).
