    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Other">
        <prj:name>Unveling the magnetized disk</prj:name>
        <prj:note>Obtain for the first time the magnetic field structure in a disk around a massive YSO at an unprecedented angular resolution (0.04arcsec or 68 AU}: the disk traced by the dust has a radius of ~200 AU). We will observe the dust continuum in full polarization at 263 GHz to achieve the needed sensitivity and angular resolution.  The dust emission is very bright, so self-calibration will be performed. We plan to use MHD simulations of magnetized disks adapted for the observed dust and polarization distribution detected by ALMA. We will use DustPol package from ARTIST to generate synthetic Stokes I, Q and U maps which will be compared with the data using the CASA simulator.  </prj:note>
